y disguised version of the fossil-fueled present. Spaceship in the Desert tells the story of Masdar, at once a "utopia" sponsored by the Emirati government, and a well-resourced company involving different actors who participated in the project, each with their own agendas and desires.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspectszUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspectszUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 0aSustainable urban developmentzUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 0aSustainable urban developmentzUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 0aTechnological innovationsxEnvironmental aspectszUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 0aTechnological innovationsxEnvironmental aspectszUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 0aUrban ecology (Sociology)zUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 0aUrban ecology (Sociology)zUnited Arab EmirateszAbū Ẓaby (Emirate). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2019z978311069632540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478002406zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478002406423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781478002406.jpg  a978-3-11-069632-5  DUK eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles